    "narrative": "Our daily offensive profile for LawDog is led by **Lawrence Butler** (73.43) and **Daulton Varsho** (70.72). **Lawrence Butler** is our standout play, leveraging an elite 15% skill boost against Michael Wacha and a favorable 10% park factor adjustment, effectively neutralizing his lower spot in the order. Similarly, **Daulton Varsho** benefits significantly from the platoon advantage against Bello, with his 13% skill boost and elevated park factor driving him into the low 70s. While **Jonathan Aranda** (67.67) and **Cal Raleigh** (67.47) provide high-floor production, **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez** (65.79) remains a core stabilizer; though his matchup against Rasmussen is neutral, his elite contact profile and the specific opportunity for stolen base production against a slower delivery ensure he stays locked in at 3B.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench centered on **Gleyber Torres** (37.95), who narrowly missed the starting cut due to a hostile matchup against Ritchie. While his order position provided a minor boost, the combination of Ritchie\u2019s elite 2.57 xERA and a punitive platoon disadvantage dropped **Gleyber Torres** below our established 40.0 efficiency floor. We are managing game caps aggressively today, and with **Geraldo Perdomo** (58.54) holding the lead-off spot against Sproat, we opted to favor the volume of the lead-off role over the marginal upside of the **Gleyber Torres** platoon profile. Note that **Taylor Ward** is a confirmed scratch due to a rainout, and we are holding **Wenceel Perez**, **Tyler Freeman**, **Will Smith**, **Bryson Stott**, **Yainer Diaz**, **Matt Chapman**, **Luis Arraez**, **Brendan Donovan**, **Jung Hoo Lee**, **Jeremiah Jackson**, **Gavin Sheets**, and **Drew Gilbert** in reserve to preserve capacity for higher-leverage outings later in the week. **Masyn Winn** (41.17) remains a high-risk start; while his score cleared the floor, he is facing a tough 3.09 xERA, and we are relying on favorable wind conditions to help compensate for the anticipated skill gap.",
